# Demo Short Story Project

This is a demonstration short story project for emacs-writing.

Type: Short Story (Science Fiction)
Status: In Progress (Draft)
Word Count: ~892 words (target: 5000)

## Files

- README.org - Project overview and metadata
- story.org - The manuscript with integrated word tracking
- notes.org - Character sketches, plot outline, and research

## Features Demonstrated

- Simple 3-section structure (Opening, Middle, Ending)
- Scene properties (PoV, Location, Timeline, Summary)
- Integrated word count tracking with org-tracktable
- Character database with properties
- Plot outline and themes
- Research notes and references
- Revision tracking
- Style notes and writing guidelines

## Story Summary

"The Last Message" is a science fiction short story about Dr. Elena Chen, 
a quantum physicist who receives a warning from her future self about a 
catastrophic experiment. The story explores themes of determinism vs. free 
will through a stable time loop paradox.
